just_use main.go

# label: TOOL
# role: encodes domain knowledge

Compiler: LynRummy-conformance .dsl scenarios → native Go (and Elm) test
code. Pipeline: parse → AST → text/template → goimports+gofmt → write →
go build verify → idempotence check. Same codegen philosophy as crudgen —
the DSL is the source of truth, the emitted .go is a build artifact.

Exported AST field names are load-bearing: text/template can only read
exported identifiers. Renaming a field without updating the templates
will produce silent empty sections.
